The paper discusses the use of OFDM in visible light communications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed use of delta-sigma modulators involves analog and optical signal processing, which falls under the category of other (cs.OH). The paper also discusses the practical advantages of the proposed system, which relates to system engineering (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) in terms of optimizing the system performance.
